27FCB7D0.Line7.6D03F: Oh, Elias. Was all this worth it, then? Truly?

294394EF.Line27.789BF: It is time to let go.

31FD8C2C.VoiceDir33.8DD12: gasps as his throat is cut

5A1F4B4A.Line1.6D03F: Taissa... I need to speak with him.

5B662869.Line21.789BF: ...of your own free will, you swore an oath to the Tree of Whispers.

6F4F3D1B.Line11.8DD12: You left me alone to cross the lines you would dare not attempt and you have nothing to show for it. You are nothing but a wasted life. Do not look to forgive me, old man, because it is you who brought us here.

8F4F1B6D.Line25.789BF: The Tree does not forget oaths, and it does not forgive debts.

A338301F.Line15.8DD12: “Was it worth it?” That is a coward’s question, Lorath. It suits you.

C2163F12.Line9.8DD12: I brought Lilith to Sanctuary. A thing no one thought possible. And when Hell rises to sweep across this world, I should be there beside her, ready to push it back.

CBF205AE.VoiceDir35.8DD12: gurgles and gasps as he bleeds out and dies

F5858B7E.Line23.8DD12: This is not the life I deserved.
